The Vice President of the United States, Kamala Harris, spoke at a private residence in Los Gatos, California. She thanked the hosts and everyone in attendance for their work in fighting for what is right. She reflected on the ongoing fight for civil rights and the need for each generation to continue the fight. Harris discussed the recent Supreme Court decision on abortion rights and expressed her disappointment. She emphasized the importance of elections and the need for Democrats to stand together and fight for their values. She highlighted the accomplishments of the Biden administration and the work that still needs to be done, including passing the Women's Health Act, voting rights legislation, and affordable childcare. Harris urged everyone to stay active and engaged in the upcoming midterm elections, as the outcome will have a significant impact on the country. She emphasized the need to fight for democracy in America.